<p>I have a little svg imagemap that has four quadrants.  When each quadrant is clicked on, it is supposed to change the opacity of a rectangle overlaying the grayscale base image.  When clicked again, the opacity goes back to 0.  It works great but it takes two clicks on each quadrant to get the thing going.</p>  <p>I have seen a lot of suggestions about using JQuery, but my understanding is that JQuery does not register onclicks in svg which is xml.</p>  <p>Here is the code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt;     &lt;svg version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" viewBox="0 0 1200 808" &gt;     &lt;image width="290" height="290" xlink:href="../includes-jar-code/_images/SquareTestGray.png"&gt;     &lt;/image&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;a xlink:href="//jarea.com/yellow"&gt;--&gt;         &lt;rect onclick="top.notify(evt)" id="svgYellow" x="0" y="0" fill="#FFFF00" opacity="0" width="145" height="145" /&gt;                &lt;text x="72" y="72" fill="red"&gt;Y&lt;/text&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;/a&gt;--&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;a xlink:href="//jarea.com/pink"&gt;--&gt;         &lt;rect onclick="top.notify(evt)" id="svgPink" x="0" y="146" fill="#FF00FF" opacity="0" width="145" height="145" /&gt;         &lt;text x="72" y="218" fill="red"&gt;P&lt;/text&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;/a&gt;--&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;a xlink:href="//jarea.com/blue"&gt;--&gt;         &lt;rect onclick="top.notify(evt)" id="svgBlue" x="146" y="0" fill="#0000FF" opacity="0" width="145" height="145" /&gt;         &lt;text x="218" y="72" fill="red"&gt;B&lt;/text&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;/a&gt;--&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;a xlink:href="//jarea.com/green"&gt;--&gt;         &lt;rect onclick="top.notify(evt)" id="svgGreen" x="146" y="146" fill="#008000" opacity="0" width="145" height="145" /&gt;         &lt;text x="218" y="218" fill="red"&gt;G&lt;/text&gt;     &lt;!--&lt;/a&gt;--&gt; &lt;/svg&gt;  &lt;script&gt;  function notify(evt){      if( document.getElementById(evt.target.id).style.opacity == "0" ) {         document.getElementById(evt.target.id).style.opacity = ".25";     } else {         document.getElementById(evt.target.id).style.opacity = "0";     } }     &lt;/script&gt;  &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Don't have a high enough reputation to post the background image.  It is a 290 x 290 px grayscale square divided evenly into 4 quadrants.</p>  <p>Your insights and suggestions are greatly appreciated.</p>